{
  "texts": [
    "The patient was admitted to the hospital.",
    "For his elevated IOP, he was treated with intravenous mannitol (20%) and oral acetazolamide, along with anti-glaucoma drops such as brimonidine, timolol, and dorzolamide.",
    "Topical steroids and cycloplegic drops (atropine) were also administered.",
    "He received an intravitreal injection of bevacizumab (1.25 mg).",
    "His IOP was still above 40 mmHg and pan-retinal photocoagulation (PRP) could not be performed due to corneal edema What kind of surgery would you perform?"
  ]
}